@node Introduction
@chapter Introduction

@cindex introduction
@cindex Instapaper
@cindex read later service

read-later is an Emacs package that provides seamless integration with
Instapaper, a popular read-it-later service. With read-later, you can:

@itemize @bullet
@item
Save URLs to your Instapaper account from anywhere in Emacs
@item
Integrate with elfeed to save RSS feed entries
@item
Use secure credential management via @code{auth-source}
@item
Add URLs interactively or directly from point
@end itemize

@section Requirements

@itemize @bullet
@item
Emacs 29.1 or higher
@item
An Instapaper account (@pxref{Setting Up Instapaper})
@item
Optional: GPG for encrypted credential storage
@end itemize

@node Installation
@chapter Installation

@cindex installation
@cindex package installation

There are several ways to install read-later, depending on your package
management preferences.

@menu
* Manual Installation::         Installing from source
* Using straight.el::           Installation with straight.el
* Using use-package::           Installation with use-package
* Spacemacs Installation::      Installing in Spacemacs
* Doom Emacs Installation::     Installing in Doom Emacs
@end menu

@node Manual Installation
@section Manual Installation

@cindex manual installation

The simplest way to install read-later is manually:

@enumerate
@item
Clone the repository or download @file{read-later.el}:

@example
git clone https://github.com/barnacleDevelopments/read-later.el
@end example

@item
Add the following to your Emacs initialization file:

@lisp
(add-to-list 'load-path "/path/to/read-later")
(require 'read-later)
@end lisp
@end enumerate

@node Using straight.el
@section Using straight.el

@cindex straight.el

If you use @code{straight.el}, add this to your configuration:

@lisp
(straight-use-package
 '(read-later :type git :host github
               :repo "barnacleDevelopments/read-later.el"))
@end lisp

@node Using use-package
@section Using use-package

@cindex use-package

For @code{use-package} with @code{straight.el}:

@lisp
(use-package read-later
  :straight (read-later :type git :host github
                         :repo "barnacleDevelopments/read-later.el")
  :commands (read-later-add-url-at-point
             read-later-interactively-add-url
             read-later-add-elfeed-entry-at-point))
@end lisp

@node Spacemacs Installation
@section Spacemacs Installation

@cindex Spacemacs

For Spacemacs users:

@enumerate
@item
Add to your @code{dotspacemacs-additional-packages} in
@code{dotspacemacs/layers}:

@lisp
(defun dotspacemacs/layers ()
  (setq-default
   dotspacemacs-additional-packages
   '((read-later :location (recipe
                             :fetcher github
                             :repo "barnacleDevelopments/read-later.el")))))
@end lisp

@item
Add keybindings in @code{dotspacemacs/user-config}:

@lisp
(defun dotspacemacs/user-config ()
  (spacemacs/set-leader-keys
    "ai a" 'read-later-add-url-at-point
    "ai u" 'read-later-interactively-add-url))
@end lisp
@end enumerate

@node Doom Emacs Installation
@section Doom Emacs Installation

@cindex Doom Emacs

For Doom Emacs users:

@enumerate
@item
Add to your @file{packages.el}:

@lisp
;; ~/.doom.d/packages.el
(package! read-later
  :recipe (:host github :repo "barnacleDevelopments/read-later.el"))
@end lisp

@item
Run @command{doom sync}, then add to your @file{config.el}:

@lisp
;; ~/.doom.d/config.el
(use-package! read-later
  :commands (read-later
             read-later-interactively-add-url
             read-later-add-url-at-point
             read-later-add-elfeed-entry-at-point)
  :init
  ;; Auth backend: 'authinfo (default) or '1password
  (setq read-later-api-auth-backend 'authinfo)
  ;; Override credential lookup host if needed (default: "www.instapaper.com")
  ;; (setq read-later-api-host "www.instapaper.com")
  :config
  (map! :leader
        (:prefix-map ("R" . "read-later")
         :desc "Open bookmarks"   "R" #'read-later
         :desc "Add URL"          "a" #'read-later-interactively-add-url
         :desc "Add URL at point" "p" #'read-later-add-url-at-point
         :desc "Setup OAuth"      "o" #'read-later-api-oauth-setup)))
@end lisp

@item
Restart Emacs.
@end enumerate

@node Configuration
@chapter Configuration

@cindex configuration
@cindex authentication
@cindex credentials

Instapapier uses Emacs' built-in @code{auth-source} library for secure
credential management.

@menu
* Setting Up Instapaper::       Creating an Instapaper account
* Configuring Authentication::  Setting up credentials in Emacs
* Testing Authentication::      Verifying your setup
@end menu

@node Setting Up Instapaper
@section Setting Up Instapaper

@cindex account creation
@cindex Instapaper account

If you don't already have an Instapaper account:

@enumerate
@item
Visit @url{https://www.instapaper.com/}
@item
Click ``Sign Up'' in the top right corner
@item
Enter your email address and choose a password
@item
Verify your email address
@end enumerate

@node Configuring Authentication
@section Configuring Authentication

@cindex auth-source
@cindex authinfo
@cindex GPG

You need to add your Instapaper credentials to an @code{auth-source} file.
There are two main options:

@menu
* Plain Text Credentials::      Using ~/.authinfo
* Encrypted Credentials::       Using ~/.authinfo.gpg (recommended)
* 1Password Credentials::       Using 1Password
@end menu

@node Plain Text Credentials
@subsection Plain Text Credentials

@cindex authinfo plain text

Create or edit @file{~/.authinfo} and add:

@example
machine www.instapaper.com login your-email@@example.com password your-password
machine instapaper-oauth login your-consumer-key password your-consumer-secret
@end example

@strong{Important:} This file stores credentials in plain text. Secure it with:

@example
chmod 600 ~/.authinfo
@end example

@node Encrypted Credentials
@subsection Encrypted Credentials (Recommended)

@cindex authinfo encrypted
@cindex GPG encryption

For better security, use an encrypted file:

@enumerate
@item
Create or edit @file{~/.authinfo.gpg}

@item
Add the same lines as the plain text version:

@example
machine www.instapaper.com login your-email@@example.com password your-password
machine instapaper-oauth login your-consumer-key password your-consumer-secret
@end example

@item
Save the file (Emacs will prompt you to encrypt it with GPG)
@end enumerate

Ensure GPG is configured in Emacs:

@lisp
(require 'epa-file)
(epa-file-enable)
@end lisp

@node 1Password Credentials
@subsection 1Password Credentials

@cindex 1Password
@cindex auth-source-1password

You can store credentials in 1Password using the @code{auth-source-1password}
package and the 1Password CLI.

@enumerate
@item
Install the 1Password CLI (@command{op}) and sign in.

@item
Install @code{auth-source-1password}:

@lisp
(use-package auth-source-1password
  :ensure t
  :config
  (auth-source-1password-enable))
@end lisp

@item
Create a 1Password item named @code{www.instapaper.com} with:
@itemize @bullet
@item A field named @code{username} containing your Instapaper email
@item A field named @code{password} containing your Instapaper password
@end itemize

@item
Create a second item named @code{instapaper-oauth} with:
@itemize @bullet
@item A field named @code{username} containing your OAuth consumer key
@item A field named @code{password} containing your OAuth consumer secret
@end itemize

@item
Configure read-later to use 1Password:

@lisp
(setq read-later-api-auth-backend '1password)
@end lisp

@end enumerate

If your 1Password item has a different name, override the lookup host:

@lisp
(setq read-later-api-host "My Instapaper Item")
@end lisp

@strong{Note:} On first use, you may be prompted for your 1Password master
password up to four times (once per field for each of the two credential items).
Subsequent calls use cached credentials. To minimize prompts, enable the desktop
app CLI integration in 1Password @clicksequence{Settings @click{} Developer @click{}
Integrate with 1Password CLI}.

@node Testing Authentication
@section Testing Authentication

@cindex testing
@cindex authentication test

After configuring your credentials, verify they work:

@example
M-x read-later-test-auth
@end example

You should see ``@samp{✓ Authentication successful!}'' in the minibuffer.

@node Usage
@chapter Usage

@cindex usage
@cindex commands

Instapapier provides several interactive commands for managing your Instapaper bookmarks.

@menu
* Viewing Bookmarks::                 View and manage your bookmarks
* Refreshing Bookmarks::              Update the bookmark list
* Adding URLs at Point::              Save URL under cursor
* Adding URLs Interactively::         Enter URL manually
* Updating Bookmark Read Progress::   Mark your bookmarks read or unread
* Archiving Bookmarks::                 Archive or Unarchive bookmark

@end menu

@node Viewing Bookmarks
@section Viewing Bookmarks

@findex read-later
@cindex bookmarks buffer
@cindex view bookmarks

To open the Instapaper bookmarks buffer:

@example
M-x read-later
@end example

This opens a tabulated list of your Instapaper bookmarks where you can:

@itemize @bullet
@item
Press @kbd{RET} to open a bookmark in your browser
@item
Press @kbd{g} to refresh the list
@item
View bookmark titles, reading progress, tags, and descriptions
@end itemize

@node Refreshing Bookmarks
@section Refreshing Bookmarks

@findex read-later-update
@cindex refresh bookmarks

If you have the bookmarks buffer open, you can refresh it:

@example
M-x read-later-update
@end example

Or simply press @kbd{g} in the bookmarks buffer.

@node Adding URLs at Point
@section Adding URLs at Point

@findex read-later-add-url-at-point
@cindex URL at point

To save a URL located at the cursor position:

@example
M-x read-later-add-url-at-point
@end example

The command will detect the URL at point and send it to Instapaper.

@node Adding URLs Interactively
@section Adding URLs Interactively

@findex read-later-interactively-add-url
@cindex interactive URL input

To manually enter a URL:

@example
M-x read-later-interactively-add-url
@end example

You'll be prompted to enter the URL in the minibuffer.

@node Updating Bookmark Read Progress
@section Marking bookmark read
@findex read-later-mark-read-at-point
@cindex interactive read update

To mark bookmark read:

@example
M-x read-later-mark-read-at-point
@end example

The bookmark at point will be updated to 100% read progress.

@section Marking bookmark unread
@findex read-later-mark-unread-at-point
@cindex interactive unread update

To mark bookmark unread:

@example
M-x read-later-mark-unread-at-point
@end example

The bookmark at point will be updated to 0% read progress.

@node Archiving Bookmarks
@section Archive bookmark
@findex read-later-archive-bookmark-at-point
@cindex interactive archive
@example
M-x read-later-archive-bookmark-at-point
@end example

The bookmark at point with be archived.

@section Unarchive bookmark
@findex read-later-unarchive-bookmark-at-point
@cindex interactive unarchive

@example
M-x read-later-unarchive-bookmark-at-point
@end example

The bookmark at point will be unarchived.

