@node Interactive Functions
@section Interactive Functions

@findex read-later
@deffn Command read-later

Open the Instapaper bookmarks buffer. Displays a tabulated list of your
bookmarks with titles, reading progress, tags, and descriptions.

In the bookmarks buffer:
@itemize @bullet
@item
Press @kbd{RET} to open a bookmark in your browser
@item
Press @kbd{g} to refresh the bookmark list
@end itemize

This is an interactive command that can be invoked with @kbd{M-x}.

@strong{Example:}
@example
M-x read-later
@end example
@end deffn

@findex read-later-update
@deffn Command read-later-update

Refresh the bookmarks buffer with the latest data from Instapaper. This
command updates the bookmark list to show any changes made on other devices
or through the Instapaper website.

This is an interactive command that can be invoked with @kbd{M-x} or by
pressing @kbd{g} in the bookmarks buffer.

@strong{Example:}
@example
M-x read-later-update
@end example
@end deffn

@findex read-later-add-url-at-point
@deffn Command read-later-add-url-at-point

Add the URL at point to Instapaper. Detects the URL under the cursor
using @code{thing-at-point} and sends it to your Instapaper account.

This is an interactive command that can be invoked with @kbd{M-x}.

@strong{Example:}
@example
M-x read-later-add-url-at-point
@end example
@end deffn

@findex read-later-interactively-add-url
@deffn Command read-later-interactively-add-url url

Prompt for a URL and add it to Instapaper. You'll be asked to enter the
URL in the minibuffer.

This is an interactive command that can be invoked with @kbd{M-x}.

@strong{Arguments:}
@table @var
@item url
The URL to add to Instapaper (prompted interactively).
@end table

@strong{Example:}
@example
M-x read-later-interactively-add-url RET
https://example.com/article RET
@end example
@end deffn

@findex read-later-add-elfeed-entry-at-point
@deffn Command read-later-add-elfeed-entry-at-point

Add the elfeed entry at point to Instapaper. This command should be used
in the elfeed search buffer. It extracts the URL from the selected feed
entry and sends it to Instapaper.

Requires the @code{elfeed} package to be installed.

This is an interactive command that can be invoked with @kbd{M-x}.

@strong{Example:}
@example
;; In elfeed-search-mode buffer
M-x read-later-add-elfeed-entry-at-point
@end example
@end deffn

@findex read-later-test-auth
@deffn Command read-later-test-auth

Test authentication with Instapaper. Sends a request to the Instapaper
authentication endpoint and displays whether authentication succeeded.

This is useful for verifying your credentials are configured correctly.

This is an interactive command that can be invoked with @kbd{M-x}.

@strong{Returns:}
Displays a message indicating success or failure.

@strong{Example:}
@example
M-x read-later-test-auth
;; => "✓ Authentication successful!"
@end example
@end deffn

@node Internal Functions
@section Internal Functions

@findex read-later-add-url
@defun read-later-add-url url

Internal function to add a URL to Instapaper. This is the core function
that handles authentication, API communication, and error handling.

@strong{Arguments:}
@table @var
@item url
The URL string to add to Instapaper.
@end table

@strong{Returns:}
The response buffer on success, or @code{nil} on error.

@strong{HTTP Status Codes:}
@table @code
@item 201
Successfully added URL
@item 400
Bad request (invalid URL format)
@item 403
Authentication failed
@end table

This function is not interactive and is meant to be called by other
read-later commands.
@end defun

@node Variables
@section Variables

@defopt read-later-api-auth-backend
The authentication backend to use when looking up credentials.

@strong{Default value:} @code{authinfo}

@strong{Valid values:}
@table @code
@item authinfo
Use @file{~/.authinfo} or @file{~/.authinfo.gpg} via Emacs' built-in
@code{auth-source} library. This is the default.
@item 1password
Use 1Password via the @code{auth-source-1password} package and the
1Password CLI. Requires @code{auth-source-1password} to be installed and
configured. @xref{1Password Credentials}.
@end table

@strong{Example:}
@lisp
(setq read-later-api-auth-backend '1password)
@end lisp
@end defopt

@defopt read-later-api-host
The host name used to look up Instapaper account credentials in
@code{auth-source}.

@strong{Default value:} @code{"www.instapaper.com"}

Override this if your credential store uses a different name for the
Instapaper entry. For example, if your 1Password item is named
@code{"Instapaper"}:

@lisp
(setq read-later-api-host "Instapaper")
@end lisp

The OAuth consumer credentials are always looked up under the host
@code{instapaper-oauth} and are not affected by this variable.
@end defopt

